			"components": [
				{
					"role": "intro",
					"layout": "dateLayout",
					"text": "Sep 20, 2015 @ 3:00 PM",
					"textStyle": "dateStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "title",
					"layout": "titleLayout",
					"text": "Designer Jean-Louis Deniot's Secrets To Timeless Style",
					"textStyle": "titleStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "intro",
					"layout": "introLayout",
					"text": "Jean-Louis Deniot's sexy, sensuous interiors are the epitome of cool.",
					"textStyle": "introStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "divider",
					"stroke": {
						"color": "#FFF0"
					},
					"layout": "blackStrokeLayout1",
					"style": "baseStrokeStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "author",
					"layout": "authorLayout",
					"text": "By Lindsey DeSimone",
					"textStyle": "authorStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "divider",
					"stroke": {
						"color": "#FFF0"
					},
					"layout": "blackStrokeLayout2",
					"style": "baseStrokeStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "body",
					"text": "He pulls together spaces that are sophisticated, seductive, and indelibly French\u2014intricate assemblages of plush fabrics, just-so vintage pieces, and one-off custom work that make you feel as if you're sitting in the chicest room in the world. \"I'm so attentive to atmosphere and the way you are going to live in a place,\" says Paris-based designer Jean-Louis Deniot, whose Left Bank studio serves clients from New York to New Delhi.\n\nThe approach is intensely layered\u2014hammered metal, veined marble, inlaid wood\u2014with no detail overlooked. Deniot has commissioned painted embellishments on the hems of curtains from a couture *petite main* for a client and trompe l'oeil skies on the walls of his own 7th arrondissement apartment. \"I've never used a plain fabric in my life, and a bare wall puts me into a panic.",
					"layout": "bodyLayout",
					"textStyle": "bodyStyleFirst",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "section",
					"layout": "slideLayout",
					"components": [
						{
							"role": "heading",
							"text": "1\\. Try to balance comfort and aesthetics",
							"layout": "heading1Layout",
							"textStyle": "heading1Style",
							"format": "markdown"
						},
						{
							"role": "container",
							"style": "photoContainerStyle",
							"components": [
								{
									"role": "image",
									"URL": "http://ver.h-cdn.co/assets/15/37/1441814490-jean-louis-deniots-timeless-interior-design-03-no-wm.jpg",
									"layout": "photoLayout",
									"animation": {
										"type": "fade_in",
										"userControllable": true,
										"initialAlpha": 0.1
									}
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"role": "photographer",
							"text": "Simon Upton",
							"layout": "creditLayout",
							"textStyle": "creditStyle"
						},
						{
							"role": "caption",
							"text": "\"When you place a sofa in the center of the room, the back has to be as attractive as the front\u2014otherwise it's like the Berlin Wall. It shouldn't be too deep either, so it doesn't dwarf a side table. **Try to balance comfort and aesthetics.**\"",
							"layout": "captionLayout",
							"textStyle": "captionStyle",
							"format": "markdown"
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"role": "section",
					"layout": "slideLayout",
					"components": [
						{
							"role": "heading",
							"text": "2\\. Don't start with furniture and finishes",
							"layout": "heading1Layout",
							"textStyle": "heading1Style",
							"format": "markdown"
						},
						{
							"role": "container",
							"style": "photoContainerStyle",
							"components": [
								{
									"role": "image",
									"URL": "http://ver.h-cdn.co/assets/15/37/1441814519-jean-louis-deniots-timeless-interior-design-01-no-wm.jpg",
									"layout": "photoLayout",
									"animation": {
										"type": "fade_in",
										"userControllable": true,
										"initialAlpha": 0.1
									}
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"role": "photographer",
							"text": "Richard Powers",
							"layout": "creditLayout",
							"textStyle": "creditStyle"
						},
						{
							"role": "caption",
							"text": "\"We **don't start with furniture and finishes**\u2014our method of attack is through the interior architecture. We compose a feeling with the envelope before we define the color of the dishes.\"",
							"layout": "captionLayout",
							"textStyle": "captionStyle",
							"format": "markdown"
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"role": "section",
					"layout": "slideLayout",
					"components": [
						{
							"role": "heading",
							"text": "3\\. A third vintage, contemporary, custom",
							"layout": "heading1Layout",
							"textStyle": "heading1Style",
							"format": "markdown"
						},
						{
							"role": "container",
							"style": "photoContainerStyle",
							"components": [
								{
									"role": "image",
									"URL": "http://ver.h-cdn.co/assets/15/37/1441813301-jean-louis-deniots-timeless-interior-design-00.jpg",
									"layout": "photoLayout",
									"animation": {
										"type": "fade_in",
										"userControllable": true,
										"initialAlpha": 0.1
									}
								}
							]
						},
						{
							"role": "photographer",
							"text": "Richard Powers",
							"layout": "creditLayout",
							"textStyle": "creditStyle"
						},
						{
							"role": "caption",
							"text": "\"My formula for furnishings is **a third vintage, a third contemporary, and a third custom** to create a link between the first two, so that it all blends together and you can't tell what's old and what's new.\"",
							"layout": "captionLayout",
							"textStyle": "captionStyle",
							"format": "markdown"
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"role": "banner_advertisement",
					"bannerType": "standard"
				}
			]
		}
